<t tx="swot.20251103101723.1">@language asciidoc
将对象组合成树形结构以表示“部分-整体”的层次结构。Composite 使得用户对单个对象和组合对象的使用具有一致性。
</t>
<t tx="swot.20251103101859.1">@language asciidoc
[plantuml, target=img/diagram-2025-11-03-101934, format=svg]
....
@startuml

' skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam roundcorner 15
skinparam shadowing false

title 组合模式 (Composite Pattern)

class Client

interface Component {
  {abstract} + operation()
  {abstract} + add(child: Component)
  {abstract} + remove(child: Component)
  {abstract} + getChild(index: int): Component
}

class Leaf {
  + operation()
  + add(child: Component)
  + remove(child: Component)
  + getChild(index: int): Component
}

class Composite {
  - children: List&lt;Component&gt;
  + operation()
  + add(child: Component)
  + remove(child: Component)
  + getChild(index: int): Component
}

Client --&gt; Component
Component &lt;|.. Leaf
Component &lt;|.. Composite
Composite o--&gt; "children *" Component

note right of Composite::operation
  // 递归调用子组件
  for (child in children) {
    child.operation();
  }
end note

note right of Leaf::add
  // 叶子节点不支持这些操作
  throw new UnsupportedOperationException();
end note

@enduml
....

List&lt;Component&gt; 不是全局的：每个 Composite 实例都有自己的 children 列表。
</t>
